  "text": "Exactly how well-founded in theory are these policy recommendations? To examine this I need to review the theory of tariff reform. Before doing so, I want to note three results which have been derived in the literature in models without a numeraire good. These results are correct as stated but I will argue later that they are not very helpful in policy contexts. So, I label them 'POMPs' for 'Potentially Misleading Propositions'! They are: 3 POMP 1: [CITATION_1] ) A tariff change of the form dt=dp*!et , d+e>0, must raise welfare.",
